    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Being a fan of &#8220;prosecco sporco&#8221;,  or &#8220;dirty prosecco&#8221;, a drink I learned to love thanks to Nigella Lawson&#39;s recent Kitchen cookbook, I&#39;ll have to try this. A splash of Campari topped off with chilled prosecco, or &#8220;prozaco&#8221; as Nigella calls it, and I&#39;m instantly relaxed. Something about the sweetly bitter edge of Campari tempered by the fizzy bite of the prosecco is appealing to me. I&#39;m not usually a fan of bitter flavors but this one definitely works for me.</p>
