    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Oh! How exciting that you just introduced everyone to Aperol! We had them when we were in Venice this past September and we are now in love. And so are all our friends that we introduce the Venetian Spritz to. The classic way they serve it in Venice is 1/3 Aperol, 1/3 Prosecco, 1/3 soda water and a wedge of orange and a green olive (which is essential, in my books). We use the castelvetrano olives because they&#39;re not so briny. </p>
<p>Thanks for the great post!</p>
