    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">redactor</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/02/by-popular-demand/#comment-25232"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-02-21T21:59:25-05:00">Monday, February 21, 2011 at 9:59 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Last fall I was in jimgermanbar in Waitsburg, Washington (just east of Walla Walla), where I had something called a Farfalle Redux. To the best of my recollection the ingredients were gin, Aperol, St. Germain, Lillet, and lemon juice. As you would expect, it was simultaneously floral, bitter, herby, and citrusy. I have tried to reproduce this at home, but I cannot get the proportions right. Or Mr. German did not tell all on the bar menu. </p>
<p>If you are ever in the Walla Walla area and you have had enough wine, jimgermanbar is an essential stop for you.</p>
    </div>

